<?xml version='1.0' standalone='yes'?>

<PLUGIN name="unraid-aicliagents" author="John White" version="2026.03.27.18" launch="Settings/AICliAgentsManager" pluginURL="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/johnpwhite/unraid-plg-aicliagents/main/unraid-aicliagents.plg" min="7.2.0" icon="assets/icons/google-gemini.png">

<CHANGES>
## 2026.03.27.18
- Fix: Stripped aggressive cleanup from SSH aliases
- Aliases now only perform home-folder mapping to prevent interference with active WebUI terminal sessions.
- Fix: Re-added surgical WAL deletion for OpenCode to resolve the persistent checkpoint loop with maximum stability.
- Fix: Minimalist rollback of shell wrapper for stability testing
- Stripped all complex environment and DB repair blocks to isolate the boot failure.
- Fix: Used %q shell-quoting for all injected variables to prevent syntax corruption from complex paths or binary arguments.
- Fix: Radical stabilization of shell environment propagation
- Swapped double-expanding heredocs for atomic 'printf' and 'echo' injections to prevent all syntax corruption.
- Fix: Implemented hybrid script generation and external environment sourcing to resolve shell syntax errors and terminal failures.
- Fix: Stabilized shell wrapper generation by hardcoding EMHTTP_DEST and refining SQLite cleanup syntax to resolve 'reconnect' failure.
- Fix: Implemented 'Sledgehammer' SQLite recovery
- Forcefully kills zombies and clears stuck WAL/SHM files before every run to end the OpenCode checkpoint error loop.
- Fix: Comprehensive permission &amp; DB repair update
- Prevents installer from resetting executable bits and adds pre-flight fixes to SSH aliases.
- Fix: Added shell-integration
- sh to the installer manifest so aliases are correctly deployed and symlinked.
- Fix: Injected terminal-side SQLite pre-flight check to resolve persistent OpenCode checkpoint failures during session reloads.
- Feat: Advanced shell integration (global aliases) and integrated User &amp; Architecture Guide links in Settings and Terminal Drawer.
- Fix: Mandatory recursive chmod for the entire agent directory on load to resolve internal EACCES errors for sub-processes (e
- g.,
- opencode).
- Fix: Mandatory binary permission check before varje terminal start to resolve 'Permission denied' even when binaries already exist in RAM.
- Fix: Resolve 'Permission denied' on agent binaries by forcing recursive 755 permissions after restoration from USB cache.
- Feat: Implemented automatic SQLite pre-flight check to Repair/Checkpoint agent databases (OpenCode, Claude, etc.) on terminal load, ensuring consistent state after RAM restoration.
- Fix: Resolve OpenCode SQLite checkpoint failures by enhancing 'Scorched Earth' process cleanup and ensuring WAL consistency during syncs.
- Fix: Synced codebase and removed redundant/corrupt icon assets. - Cleanup: Standardized on google-gemini
- png for all internal references (settings, drawer, etc).
- Fix: Resolved Permission Denied for binaries.
- Fix: Resolved 'Permission denied' errors by forcing executable bits on agent binaries and symlink targets
- Fix: Reinforced recursive 755 permissions across the isolated agent environments
- Fix: Fixed Gemini icon content and reverted to original filename (google-gemini
- png).
- Fix: Reverted Gemini icon to the original google-gemini.png filename for consistency
- Fix: Overwrote corrupted icon with valid sparkle asset to resolve 'Not showing' issue
- Internal: Updated UI build to use cache-busted icon URLs
- Fix: Restored Gemini icon from valid src/ asset.
- Fix: Restored Gemini icon by overwriting corrupted 404 placeholder with valid asset
- Internal: Standardized agent icon paths for consistent WebUI appearance
- Fix: Corrected Gemini binary name to gemini; Fix: OS disk sync; Fix: Broader discovery.
- Fix: Corrected Gemini binary name from aicli to gemini (Resolved installation health check failure)
- Fix: Implemented OS disk cache synchronization after agent deployment
- Fix: Enhanced post-install discovery with broader filesystem scanning
- Fix: Resolved PHP Fatal Error; Fix: Simplified isolated installation; Fix: Added exhaustive discovery logging.
- Fix: Resolved PHP Fatal Error in logging engine (aicli_prune_log)
- Fix: Simplified isolated installation to resolve scoped package linkage issues
- Fix: Added exhaustive filesystem discovery to identify NPM output location
- Fix: Switched to tar-pipe deployment; Fix: Added pre-deployment discovery logging.
- Fix: Switched to high-fidelity tar-pipe deployment for isolated agents
- Fix: Added pre-deployment discovery logging to verify NPM package contents
- Fix: Resolved potential symlink breakage during agent RAM migration
- Fix: Increased UI log limit; Fix: Added verbose deployment logging to identify missing binary source.
- Fix: Increased UI log viewing limit to 250 lines (respecting new log_max_lines setting)
- Fix: Switched to verbose cp -av for deployment to pinpoint file transfer failures
- Fix: Added source tree logging before deployment to verify NPM output presence
- Fix: Enforced log management; Fix: Resolved stale file status cache; Fix: Forced icon cache busting (gemini-v1
- Fix: Enforced log management with user-configurable max size (default 50MB)
- Fix: Resolved stale file status cache affecting binary verification
- Fix: Forced icon cache busting with new asset naming (gemini-v1.png)
- Fix: Reinforced agent discovery with binary path fallbacks; Fix: Enhanced installation logging; Fix: Improved icon path stability.
- Fix: Reinforced agent discovery with binary path fallbacks
- Fix: Enhanced installation logging with full NPM output capture
- Fix: Improved icon path stability to resolve display issues
- Fix: Definitive installation fix with environment isolation and clean workspace state; Fix: Resolved PHP mkdir() errors during background installations.
- Fix: Definitive installation fix with environment isolation and clean workspace state
- Fix: Resolved PHP mkdir() errors during background installations
- Fix: Critical installation logic to force dependency linking into
- bin; Fix: Added icon cache busting to force display of new Gemini assets; Fix: Reinforced background install environment with explicit PATH injection.
- Fix: Critical installation logic to force dependency linking into .bin (Resolved 'Binary missing' error)
- Fix: Added icon cache busting to force display of new Gemini assets
- Fix: Reinforced background install environment with explicit PATH injection
- Fix: Use rsync for agent deployment to ensure hidden files (
- bin) and permissions are preserved; Fix: Reverted Gemini icon filename to google-gemini
- png; Fix: Added binary existence verification to the installation process.
- Fix: Definitive agent isolation restoration in storage
- sh (Resolved dependency clobbering); Fix: Standardized Gemini icon filename to gemini-cli
- png to match registry ID; Fix: Improved installer robustness by using absolute paths for node/npm inside backend jobs; Fix: Cleaned up legacy bin/node_modules correctly across all states
